      • parse

        public void parse​(java.io.BufferedReader br)
           throws java.io.FileNotFoundException,
                  java.net.MalformedURLException,
                  java.io.IOException,
                  java.lang.Exception
        Big-O notation - O(n)

        Parses a text file into a set of words.

        It uses a space or newline as a delimiter. All non-word characters are removed. It is case insensitive. All words are parsed to the set of lower case words.

        Specified by:
        parse in interface Parsable
        Specified by:
        parse in class Parser
        Parameters:
        br - BufferedReader
        Throws:
        java.io.FileNotFoundException - if the file does not exist, is a directory rather than a regular file, or for some other reason cannot be opened for reading.
        java.net.MalformedURLException - a malformed URL has occurred
        java.io.IOException - if an I/O error occurs.
        java.lang.Exception - other exception
